Farming communities near the Du Toitskloof Pass have been evacuated due to a raging wild fire.Helicopters are continuin to use water bombs on the vegetation that had caught fire on Thursday.Officials have said that the fire spread along unburnt areas.Traffic officers have also lined the road to assist in clearing the area for emergency vehicles.Western Cape Traffic Chief Kenny Africa says motorists are being redirected.At least 30 firefighters have the assistance of waterbombing helicopters.